The read-only <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/Screen" title="The Screen interface represents a screen, usually the one on which the current window is being rendered, and is obtained using window.screen."><code>Screen</code></a> interface's <code><strong>availHeight</strong></code> property returns the height, in CSS pixels, of the space available for Web content on the screen. Since <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/Screen" title="The Screen interface represents a screen, usually the one on which the current window is being rendered, and is obtained using window.screen."><code>Screen</code></a> is exposed on the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window" title="The Window interface represents a window containing a DOM document; the document property points to the DOM document loaded in that window."><code>Window</code></a> interface's <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/screen" title="The Window property screen returns a reference to the screen object associated with the window. The screen object, implementing the Screen interface, is a special object for inspecting properties of the screen on which the current window is being rendered."><code>window.screen</code></a> property, you access <code>availHeight</code> using <code>window.screen.availHeight</code>.